// Both ensures clauses pin r1@ and r2@ to `Map::total(|k: K| id_zero@)`, which
// unfolds to `Set::full().mk_map(|k| id_zero@)`. Force per-key instantiation of
// the mk_map axiom so that every key yields `id_zero@` in both views, witness
// that both domains are `Set::full()`, and then close the gap with Map
// extensionality (`=~=`). Each assertion is something Verus must verify
// against the ensures hypotheses; nothing is assumed on faith.
assert(forall|k: K| #[trigger] r1@[k] == id_zero@);
assert(forall|k: K| #[trigger] r2@[k] == id_zero@);
assert(r1@.dom() =~= r2@.dom());
assert(r1@ =~= r2@);
